obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (28023)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28023&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Pondicherry`
  line `(Administration) Act, 1962.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of Pondicherry.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 16th day of August, 1962.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (28024)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28024&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "Administrator" means the Administrator of Pondicherry appointed by the President under`
  line `article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) "appointed day" means the 16th day of August, 1962, being the date of entry into force of the`
  line `Treaty of Cession;`
  line
  line `(c) "former French Establishments" mean the territories which immediately before the appointed`
  line `day were comprised in the French Establishments in India known as Pondicherry, Karikal, Mahe and`
  line Yanam;
  line
  line `(d) "High Court" means the High Court at Madras;`
  line
  line `(e) "law" means any Act, Ordinance, Regulation, rule, order, bye-law, decree or other provision`
  line `(by whatever name called) having the force of law;`
  line
  line `(f) "Pondicherry" means the Union territory comprising the territories of the former French`
  line Establishments;
  line
  line `(g) "Treaty of Cession" means the treaty concluded between France and India on the 28th day of`
  line `May, 1956, establishing the cession of the French Establishments by France to India in full`
  line sovereignty.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (28025)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Officers and functionaries in relation to Pondicherry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28025&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the powers of the`
  line `Central Government to appoint from time to time such officers and authorities as may be necessary for`
  line `the administration of Pondicherry, all courts, tribunals, authorities and officers, whether in India or in the`
  line `former French Establishments, who immediately before the appointed day, were exercising lawful`
  line `functions in connection with the administration of those Establishments or any part thereof, including the`
  line `Council of Government and the Representative Assembly, shall, unless otherwise directed at any time by`
  line `the Central Government or the Administrator in relation to any such court, tribunal, authority or officer,`
  line `or until other provision is made by law, continue to exercise in connection with the administration of`
  line `Pondicherry their respective powers and jurisdiction and perform their respective duties and functions in`
  line `the same manner and to the same extent as before the appointed day with such altered designation, if any,`
  line `as that Government may determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (28026)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Continuance of existing laws and their-adaptation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28026&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) All laws in force immediately before`
  line `the appointed day in the former French Establishments or any part thereof shall continue to be in force in`
  line `Pondicherry until amended or repealed by a competent Legislature or other competent authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that references in any such law to the President or Government of the French Republic shall`
  line `be construed as references to the Central Government, references to the Governor of the French`
  line `Establishments in India, to the Commissioner of the Republic for the French Establishments in India, to`
  line `the Chief Commissioner for the French Establishments, to the Chief Commissioner of the State of`
  line `Pondicherry or to the Chief Commissioner, Pondicherry, shall be construed as references to the`
  line `Administrator of Pondicherry and references to the State of Pondicherry shall be construed as references`
  line `to Pondicherry.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of facilitating the application of any such law in relation to the administration of`
  line `Pondicherry and for the purpose of bringing the provisions of any such law into accord with the`
  line `provisions of the Constitution, the Central Government may, within three years from the appointed day,`
  line `by order, make such adaptations and modifications, whether by way of repeal or amendment, as may be`
  line `necessary or expedient and thereupon every such law shall have effect subject to the adaptations and`
  line `modifications so made.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (28027)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Property and assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28027&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `For the avoidance of doubt, it is hereby declared that all property and assets`
  line `within Pondicherry which, immediately before the appointed day, vested in the Government of the French`
  line `Republic shall, save as otherwise expressly provided in the Treaty of Cession, vest in the Union.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (28028)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Rights and obligations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28028&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of the Treaty of Cession, all rights, liabilities`
  line `and obligations of the Government of the French Republic in relation to or arising out of the`
  line `administration of the former French Establishments shall, as from the appointed day, be the rights,`
  line `liabilities and obligations of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (28029)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Continuance of existing taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28029&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `All taxes, duties, cesses and fees which, immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, were being lawfully levied in the former French Establishments or any part thereof shall`
  line `continue to be levied in Pondicherry and to be applied to the same purposes, until other provision is made`
  line `by a competent Legislature or other competent authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (28030)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to extend enactments to Pondicherry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28030&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, extend with such restrictions and modifications as it thinks fit, to Pondicherry and`
  line `enactment which is in force in a State at the date of the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (28031)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Extension of the jurisdiction of Madras High Court to Pondicherry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28031&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `As from the 6th day of`
  line `November, 1962, the jurisdiction of the High Court shall extend to Pondicherry.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (28032)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Jurisdiction of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Madras State (Alteration of Name) A.L.O., 1970 (G.S.R. 112 of 1970) for "Madras".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28032&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of`
  line `section 9, the High Court shall have, in respect of Pondicherry, all such jurisdiction as under the law in`
  line `force immediately before the appointed day was exercisable in respect of the former French`
  line `Establishments by the Cour de Cassation, the Cour Superieur d' Arbitrage and the Counseil d' Etat of`
  line `France:`
  line
  line `Provided that while determining appeals from decisions of courts and tribunals in Pondicherry, the`
  line `High Court shall, as far as may be, follow the same procedure and have the same power to pass any`
  line `judgment, decree or order thereon, as it follows and has while determining appeals from decisions of`
  line `courts in the State of ^1[Tamil Nadu].`
  line
  line `(2) All appeals and other proceedings from or in respect of any judgment, decree or order of any court`
  line `or tribunal in the former French Establishments pending immediately before the appointed day before the`
  line `Cour de Cassation or the Cour Superieur d' Arbitrage or the Counseil d' Etat of France and all original`
  line `proceedings in relation to those Establishments pending immediately before the appointed day before the`
  line `Counseil d' Etat shall, by virtue of this Act, stand transferred to the High Court and shall be disposed of`
  line `by the High Court in the exercise of jurisdiction conferred on it by this Act, as if such appeals and other`
  line `proceedings had been filed before the High Court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--All appeals and other proceedings filed before the appointed day but not transmitted to`
  line `the Cour de Cassation or the Cour Superieur d' Arbitrage or the Counseil d' Etat shall be deemed to be`
  line `appeals or proceedings, as the case may be, pending before the Court for the purposes of this sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (28033)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Advocates entitled to practise before High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28033&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961), but subject to such rules as may be framed by the High Court, any`
  line `person who is entitled to practise before the Tribunal Superieur d' Appeal at Pondicherry shall be`
  line `recognised as an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court in relation to cases coming before the`
  line `High Court from Pondicherry.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (28034)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of High Court to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28034&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may, from time to time, make rules,`
  line `consistent with this Act, to provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the translation of any papers filed in the High Court and the preparation of paper books for`
  line `hearing all appeals and the copying, typing or printing of any such papers or translation and the`
  line `recovery from the persons at whose instance or on whose behalf papers are filed of the expenses`
  line `thereby incurred;`
  line
  line `(b) the court-fees payable for instituting proceedings in the High Court, the fees to be charged for`
  line `processes issued by the High Court or by any officer of the court and the amount payable in any`
  line `proceeding in the High Court in respect of fees of the advocate of any party to such proceedings;`
  line
  line `(c) the procedure to be followed in the High Court;`
  line
  line `(d) the approval, admission, enrolment, removal and suspension of advocates from Pondicherry.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (28035)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Validation of certain orders and decrees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28035&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every order or decree purported to have been`
  line `made by the Cour de Cassation, the Cour Superieur d' Arbitrage or the Counseil d' Etat of France during`
  line `the period commencing on the first day of November, 1954, and ending on the appointed day, in any`
  line `appeal or other proceeding from, or in respect of any judgment, decree or order of any court, tribunal or`
  line `other authority in the former French Establishments shall be deemed to have been validly made, in`
  line `accordance with law; and shall for all purposes have effect as if it were an order or a decree made by the`
  line `High Court in the exercise of the jurisdiction conferred by this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any decision has been rendered`
  line `after the 17th March, 1960, by any court in France in any case in which the respondent had no`
  line `opportunity to appear for want of service of summons transmitted through the Administration of the`
  line `former French Establishments, such decision shall be deemed never to have been rendered and shall be`
  line `deemed to be pending before the court by which such decision was rendered and accordingly stand`
  line `transferred to the High Court or, as the case may be, to the court in Pondicherry corresponding to the`
  line `court in France in which the case shall be deemed to be pending.`
  line
  line `(3) As soon as may be after the 6th day of November, 1962, the Administrator shall transmit to the`
  line `High Court or, as the case may be, to the corresponding court, the record of every such case as is referred`
  line `to in sub-section (2), together with a certificate that the summons in that case was not served on the`
  line respondent.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (28036)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Limitation for appeals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28036&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The periods of limitation for appeals to the High Court shall be as`
  line `set out below:—`
  line
  line S.
  line No.
  line `Description of appeal. Period of`
  line limitation.
  line `Time from which period begins to`
  line run.
  line
  line `1. Civil Appeal against any judgment or order. 90 days The date of the judgment or order.`
  line
  line `2. Criminal Appeal against a sentence of death. 7 days The date of sentence.`
  line
  line `3. Criminal Appeal against any sentence or order`
  line `other than a sentence of death.`
  line `30 days The date of the sentence or order.`
  line
  line `4. Criminal Appeal against an order of acquittal. 90 days The date of the order of acquittal.`
  line
  line `5. Labour Appeal under section 207 of the French`
  line `Labour Code, 1952.`
  line `30 days The date of the judgment or order.`
  line
  line `6. Labour Appeal under section 216 of the French`
  line `Labour Code, 1952.`
  line `30 days The date on which the report and`
  line `the recommendation of the`
  line `expert are communicated to the`
  line `party appealing.`
  line
  line `7. Appeal against a judgment or order of the`
  line `Administrative Tribunal at Pondicherry.`
  line `90 days The date of the judgment or order.`
  line
  line `(2) Except in the case of a Criminal Appeal against a sentence of death, in computing the period of`
  line `limitation, the time taken for obtaining a certified copy of the judgment, order, report and`
  line `recommendation, appealed against, as the case may be, shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of an appeal preferred by an accused person under sentence and in custody, the date on`
  line `which he lodges the memorandum of appeal with the Superintendent of the Jail in which he is detained`
  line `shall be deemed to be the date of presentation of the appeal in the High Court.`
  line
  line `(4) Any appeal may be admitted after the period of limitation prescribed therefor when the appellant`
  line `satisfies the Court that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (28037)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Saving of limitation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28037&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `In computing the period of limitation under section 14 or`
  line `under any other law, any period during which an appeal could not be filed or a proceeding could not be`
  line `instituted because the jurisdiction of the High Court did not extend to Pondicherry shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (28038)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Rule of construction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28038&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `References in any law in force in Pondicherry to the Cour de Cassation,`
  line `the Court Superieur d' Arbitrage or the Counsel d' Etat shall be construed as references to the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (28039)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28039&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of facilitating the application of any law in relation to`
  line `Pondicherry, any court or other authority may construe any such law in such manner not affecting the`
  line `substance, as may be necessary or proper to adapt it to the matter before the court or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (28040)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Effect of other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28040&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding anything`
  line `inconsistent therewith contained in any other law in force in Pondicherry.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (28041)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28041&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make any such`
  line `provisions as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the difficulty.`
  line
  line `(2) Any order under sub-section (1) may be made so as to be restrospective to any date not earlier`
  line `than the appointed day`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (28042)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076&sectionId=28042&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00005_196249_1517807318076
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Pondicherry (Administration) Ordinance, 1962 (8 of 1962), is`
  line `hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
